Based on the UV–vis spectra in Fig. S6, we could calculate the concentration of MB in the solution by using the absorbance peak at 660 nm. The degradation efficiency of MB can be defined by formula (1). The control experiments were carried out in dark with the addition of 1CDs@OHCu catalyst and the variation of absorbance could be omitted (Fig. 4
                     a). When the UV-light was on, the concentration of MB decreased rapidly in 1 h. While, in OHCu system, MB remained a high concentration even after 3 h irradiation. The degradation rate of MB by OHCu and 1CDs@OHCu is 37.4 % and 88.2 %, confirming that CDs modification could greatly improve the photocatalytic efficiency. Compared with the reported catalysts [44–51], 1CDs@OHCu shows the excellent photocatalytic degradation performance for MB (Table 1
                     ).
